The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC, has reported 452 new cases of COVID19 in 14 states. The Centre on its Twitter handle @NCDCGov Tuesday night stated that Lagos, Oyo and Delta recorded 209, 67 and 37, respectively. The new cases recorded by each state is as follows: Lagos-209Oyo-67Delta-37Ogun-36FCT-22Abia-20Enugu-16Bauchi-15Kaduna-8Ondo-8Osun-7Imo-3Benue-3Borno-1 According to the tweet, Nigeria has a total 21,371 confirmed cases, with 7,338 discharged and 533 deaths.